HEADWORD: Roughscuff
<hw>Rough"scuff</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Rough</ets>
+ <ets>scuff</ets>.]</ety> <def>A rough, coarse fellow; collectively,
the lowest class of the people; the rabble; the riffraff.</def>
<mark>[Colloq. U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

